Defendant Donte D Smith in court with attorney Christopher Paul Ehrfurth.  Paul Michael Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

 Court has found state has complied with victim notification.

   Defendant sentenced to serve SEVEN MONTHS in the House of Correction , CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE, with credit for ONE DAYS time served. RELEASE  privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply FOR DRC OR INMATE WORK RELEASE, COURT OBJECTS TO ES.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of TWELVE MONTHS .
Conditions:  
*MAINTAIN ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY/USE OF ALCOHOL OR ANY CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE UNLESS HAVE A VALID PRESCRIBTION
*AODA/ANY TREATMENT DEEMED APPROPRIATE
*MAY NOT POSSESS ANY DRUG PARAPHERNALIA
*MAY NOT POSSESS FIREARM, AMMUNITION, MAGAZINE, HOLSTER, BODY ARMOR
*MAY NOT BE IN AN AUTOMOBILE  WHERE A GUN IS PRESENT
*PARTICIPATIE IN HSED OR GED PROGRAM
*MAINTAIN FULL TIME EMPLOYMENT
*PAY All MANDATORY DNA  charges, victim/witness fees,  COSTS DURING TERM OF PROBATION OR CIVIL JUDGMENT SHALL BE ENTERED AGAINST THE DEFENDANT
*Court ordered condition time in the amount of 17 days, STAYED AND TO BE USED AS SUCH,   1st violation  7 days , 2nd violation 10 days with release privileges for DRC and inmate work, no good time credit on the condition time. Court objects to ES.  

 Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
JusticePoint Pretrial Services Report dated 01-14-2016 received and filed.

Plea Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The defendant was advised of his Constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea; clarifications set forth by defense.   Due to answers put forth by the defendant during plea colloquy the Court to pass this matter to allow defense to confer with defendant as to posture of this case.


CASE RECALLED AT APPROXIMATELY 4:04 P.M......SAME APPEARANCES....

Plea colloquy resumed.   Defendant pled GUILTY and examined by the Court as to the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Jury Trial date of 1-04-16 VACATED at this time.


Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, any victims, and the defendant. Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 3 BUSINESS days in advance of the sentencing. 

Case adjourned for Sentencing hearing, branch 17.

AMENDED INFORMATION FILED.

COUNT 1 AMENDED to: POSSESSION OF THC (TETRAHYDROCANNABINOLS), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 961.41(3g)(e), a Misdemeanor.
